page.title: 11INTRODUCTION
page.content: Our block is situated to the south to the south west of the Warwickshire town of Royal Leamington Spa.It is bordered by the village of Harbury to the East,Bishops Tachbrook to the South and Radford Semele to the North.It is crossed to the South by the main Birmingham-London (Paddington) railway line and to the North by the Grand Union Canal. It is largely an agricultural area with two residential squares which contain an expanding residential area known as Whitnash which at one stage was an independent village two miles to the South of Leamington Spa.It now contains many new starter homes occupied by young couples who work in Leamington or Coventry. There are several farms in the block many of them having natural boundaries in the Fosse Way.
